entry.title: Perga spp.
entry.content: Sawfly (perga spp.) Two possibility: Perga affinis or Perga dorsalis. In "Pests, Diseases, Ailments and Allies of Australian Plants" book by David Jones (2015), page 284 and 285, Perga dorsalis is longer (up to 7cm) than Perga affinis (up to 4cm), and has prominent bristly white hairs.

entry.title: Egretta novaehollandiae, Rhagodia candolleana subsp. candolleana
entry.content: White-faced heron on the bank of Maribyrnong River, near Newell's Paddock Wetlands. A regular visitor to the area. The bush in front of the bird is Rhagodia candolleana (Seaberry Saltbush). Common plants on the riverbank, probably planted or from seed of a plant planted by Melbourne Water.
